    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lieberman Will Run With Gore; First Jew on a Major U.S. Ticket'' (front page, Aug. 8):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lieberman Will Run With Gore; First Jew on a Major U.S. Ticket'' (front page, Aug. 8):</p>
        <p>In his acceptance speech at the Republican convention, George W. Bush called for inclusiveness. Now Al Gore has led the way. Win or lose, there is no question that Mr. Gore's bold and courageous stroke of choosing an observant Jew to be his running mate has moved the American envelope in a striking new direction.</p>
        <p>We have all been challenged to rise above fear and bigotry. We will all be winners if we meet that challenge.</p>
        <p>IRA GREENFEST  Teaneck, N.J., Aug. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
